<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 19 at 6:04PM EDT  by NWS Baltimore/Washington</headline>
<description>...SNOW SHOWERS WITH REDUCED VISIBILITY MAY IMPACT TRAVEL THIS
EVENING...
Scattered heavy snow showers will continue to impact the area
through the early evening and may disrupt travel. Visibilities
may drop quickly to less than a quarter of a mile within the snow
showers and roads may become snow covered and slippery. If
driving, slow down and increase following distance. Consider
delaying travel if a heavy snow shower is expected to impact your
location.</description>
